<HEADLINE> Gov. Ventura To Appear on Soap Opera  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) -- Gov. Jesse Ventura has found another perk
to being the country's first professional wrestler-turned-governor.
</P>
<P>
   He's been invited to make a guest appearance on his favorite
television soap opera, and he gets to play himself.
</P>
<P>
   The governor's office announced Friday that Ventura will tape a
segment of CBS's ''The Young and the Restless'' in Los Angeles on
June 14. The episode is to air later this month.
</P>
<P>
   Ventura, who says he got hooked on soap operas during his days
as a professional wrestler, says his favorite character is the
brooding and much-married millionaire Victor Newman, played by Eric
Braeden. When Braeden celebrated his 20th anniversary on the show
earlier this year, he got a surprise call from Ventura.
</P>
<P>
   The governor's TV stops are part of a seven-day trip to
California that starts June 10.
</P>
<P>
   Before being elected governor, the former professional wrestler
and radio talk show host appeared in several movies, including
''Predator.''
</P>
