<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-03 17:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgian Hiker Dies In Grand Canyon  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GRAND CANYON NATIONAL PARK, Ariz. (AP) -- A Belgian backpacker
hiking in midday heat died on a backcountry trail in the Grand
Canyon.
</P>
<P>
   The man and three companions were on a three-day hike of the
Tonto Trail when he began having problems Friday. The other
backpackers hiked to the Colorado River and asked a commercial
rafting group to call for help about 4:30 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Rangers arrived by helicopter and declared the man dead at the
scene. The cause and circumstances of his death are being
investigated.
</P>
<P>
   The other backpackers told rangers they had difficulty locating
water and changed their itinerary to reach the Colorado River.
</P>
<P>
   The Tonto Trail traverses a large plateau about 2,000 feet above
the river on the south wall of the canyon. It is exposed with
little protection from the sun. Daytime high temperatures have been
over 100 degrees in the area.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
