<HEADLINE> Highland Gold Wins L.A. Handicap  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Highland Gold, an 8-1 long shot after
finishing a distant second to Mr. Doubledown two weeks ago at
Golden Gate Fields, won the $107,100 Los Angeles Handicap on
Saturday at Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   Ridden for the first time by Chris McCarron, Highland Gold
closed strongly to beat Mellow Fellow by 1\ lengths. The
Kentucky-bred son of Slew o' Gold covered six furlongs in 1:09 and
paid $20.40, $8.40 and $5.20.
</P>
<P>
   The win was Highland Gold's first since 1998 and the $64,260
winner's purse raised his career earnings to $217,805 in 16 starts
for co-owners Jerry Hellendorfer and George Todardo.
</P>
<P>
   Mellow Fellow, ridden by Martin Pedroza, edged Your Halo by a
nose for second and paid $9.00 and $6.80.
</P>
<P>
   Your Halo, ridden by Garrett Gomez, paid $5.00 to show.
</P>
<P>
   Gomez filed a protest against Highland Gold for interference at
the start of the race, however stewards denied the claim, saying
that last-place finisher Old Topper was responsible instead of
Highland Gold.
</P>
</TEXT>
