<HEADLINE> Angola Explosion Kills 12  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LUANDA, Angola (AP) -- Twelve people were killed when teen-agers
brought a discarded missile into a crowded displaced persons camp
and the device exploded, state radio RNA reported Saturday. Another
52 people were injured.
</P>
<P>
   The blast Friday was the latest deadly incident caused by
discarded weapons from Angola's protracted civil war. Unmarked
minefields regularly cause deaths among civilians.
</P>
<P>
   The incident occurred at a camp near Malanje, about 190 miles
east of the capital, Luanda, RNA reported.
</P>
<P>
   Several teen-agers reportedly were playing with the missile when
it went off. They were killed immediately and others were
hospitalized with shrapnel wounds, according to RNA. No further
information was available.
</P>
<P>
   The Angolan government has been fighting UNITA rebels in a
two-decade civil war. Some 2 million people have been driven from
their homes by the fighting.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
