Montreal Expos beat the Baltimore Orioles 7-4 tonight for their fourth straight
win. Baltimore lost its 19th straight game in Canada despite a two-run homer by
Albert Belle and back-to-back homers in the fourth by B.J. Surhoff and Charles
Johnson.
AP NewsBrief by MARIA CODER 
